        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Stretched canvases and framed artwork require large used boxes with generous interior cushioning. Lay canvases horizontally to prevent warping. Use foam corner protectors and bubble wrap around frames. Double-wall boxes prevent crushing during truck transport within Selangor or across Malaysia.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Multilayer Padding for Fine Art</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Layer protection: kraft paper → bubble wrap → foam padding → artwork → foam padding → bubble wrap → kraft paper inside boxes. This multi-layer approach costs less with used boxes while ensuring paintings survive the move from Cheras, Kajang, or KL studios.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Moisture Control for Tropical Climate Storage</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Malaysia's humidity threatens artwork. Place silica gel packets in boxes to maintain stable moisture levels during moving and storage. Used boxes with moisture barriers keep paintings and drawings safe from mold and discoloration.</p>
